data:
PROJECT’S PARTICIPANTS– graduates of auto-technician, electro-technician, cook-waiter and secretary professions.

PROJECT’S DURATION
2015 06 01 – 2016 06 01, total 12 months. There will be two internships: to United Kingdom and Malta. Total number of participants – 20 graduates.

PROJECTS’ PARTNERS:
• Elektrėnai Vocational Training Centre (EPMC, coordinator)
• Kaišiadorys School of Business and Technology (KTVM)
• Aukštadvaris Agricultural School (AŽŪM)
• Šilutė Agricultural School (ŠŽŪM)
• International Mobility Travel Limited (United Kingdom)
• IZI Ltd. (Malta)

PROJECT’S MAIN GOAL
During the internships provide graduates with possibilities to acquire real work place practice and deficient practical professional skills and competences as well as achieve better employment opportunities, educate entrepreneurship, initiative, cultural understanding and self-confidence.

OTHER OBJECTIVES
• to educate the following specific professional competences of participants;
-for auto-technicians: to be able to maintain chassis and steering systems of right-side steering model cars’ (in United Kingdom and Malta)
- for electro-technicians: to be able to install electricity installation in areas of higher humidity, its protection against surge and fluctuation of voltage (in United Kingdom and Malta)
- for cooks-waiters: to be able to make dishes, containing seafood, serve them properly to customers (in Malta); to be able to make breakfast dishes, serve customers during the breakfast (in united Kingdom)
- for secretaries: to be able to serve customers properly in English and communicate with international clients, administer company’s social networks;
• In real work places educate new common professional competences and improve the ones already acquired, especially taking into consideration their contribution to labour market of today;
• Try to achieve that real work experience and acquired competences will be acknowledged in whole EU;
• To create the environment, where participants could acquire entrepreneurship and initiative skills, self-sufficiency, abilities to work in business and different situations;
• Try to achieve better employment opportunities of participants, improve their career prospects;
• To raise the level of participants’ self-confidence, self-esteem and sociability, to educate participants’ awareness and understanding of other cultures, tolerance;
• To improve participants’ foreign language and communicative skills in foreign environment, team-work abilities, broaden cultural outlook.

EXPECTED PROJECT’S RESULTS
• Completed professional training under the internship programs;
• Acquired real work experience;
• Acquired internship’s evaluation certificates – Europasses, certificates of hosting organizations and project’s coordinator;
• Made reports of internships;
• Raised level of the participants’ professional competences according to their professional requirements;
• In real workplaces improved practical skills of participants giving better integration possibilities into labour markets;
• Improved language and communication skills of participants;
• Raised level of participants’ self-confidence, initiative skills, entrepreneurship, sociability as well as tolerance and cultural awareness;

IMPACT
Graduates in real work places will acquire new specific professional competences and improve the ones already acquired, especially taking into consideration their contribution to labour market of today. While having practice in companies, participants will acquire entrepreneurship and initiative skills, self-sufficiency and abilities to adjust to labour market in any country. Participants will improve their foreign language skills, team work abilities, raise the level of self-confidence, self-esteem, feel themselves stronger psychologically before entering labour market.

Impact for participating organisations:
• Raised the level of international collaboration
• Improved teaching process because of possibilities to acquire experience in real work places during the internships
• Raised the level of collaboration between educational organisations and business
• Organisations’ staff will improve their management skills and competences

Long lasting impact for participants will be assured by Europass and other acknowledgement certificates, which will strengthen their diplomas, give better employment opportunities.

DISSEMINATION
Project’s dissemination will be addressed to entrepreneurs, youth, local authorities and society of Elektrenai, Kaisiadorys, Trakai, Silute and surrounding districts; present and future students of EPMC, KTVM, AŽŪM and ŠŽŪM, their parents, teachers and school’s community; potential trainees of hosting organizations.
Methods of project’s dissemination: articles in web-pages and regional newspapers, stands and booklets about project, presentations of the internships and consideration of project’s results.
